WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:09.009
{\an8}(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Free Gift Cards and Tech Items with
Southwest Points: www.fairylandshop.me

3
00:00:54.220 --> 00:00:56.222
{\an8}♪

4
00:01:49.901 --> 00:01:51.903
(theme concludes)

5
00:01:53.655 --> 00:01:56.696
(dramatic music playing)

6
00:01:56.700 --> 00:01:58.743
(horse neighs)

7
00:02:16.302 --> 00:02:20.181
♪

8
00:02:28.982 --> 00:02:30.938
(music fades out)

9
00:02:30.942 --> 00:02:32.314
Humfrey Lefford:
The Golden Tooth

10
00:02:32.318 --> 00:02:34.984
is honored to receive
you. my Lord Lannister.

11
00:02:34.988 --> 00:02:39.321
I have 500 fighting men. armed

12
00:02:39.325 --> 00:02:42.408
- and full of spirit.
- I bring a thousand knights of my own.

13
00:02:42.412 --> 00:02:46.078
and seven times as many
archers and men-at-arms.

14
00:02:46.082 --> 00:02:48.789
By the time we are finished
with the Riverland scum.

15
00:02:48.793 --> 00:02:51.296
the Red Fork will
have earned its name.

16
00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:55.759
We are ready to march at
your command. my lord.

17
00:02:56.509 --> 00:02:59.342
I suppose you will make
for Harrenhal at once.

18
00:02:59.346 --> 00:03:02.015
I want you to send a
raven to King's Landing.

19
00:03:02.724 --> 00:03:05.973
Tell my brother we
are ready to march

20
00:03:05.977 --> 00:03:09.810
as soon as Prince Aemond
is able to join us...

21
00:03:09.814 --> 00:03:11.316
on Vhagar.

22
00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:16.525
And until the prince
makes his answer. my lord?

23
00:03:16.529 --> 00:03:18.819
My men have had a long march.

24
00:03:18.823 --> 00:03:21.322
They are most eager to
embrace the hospitality

25
00:03:21.326 --> 00:03:24.496
- of your keep.
- (horses neighing)

26
00:03:27.874 --> 00:03:29.876
(lion roars)

27
00:03:37.092 --> 00:03:40.095
He dares to summon me!

28
00:03:40.845 --> 00:03:42.681
"With haste"?

29
00:03:43.264 --> 00:03:45.179
Are the Lannisters so diminished
that they cannot march

30
00:03:45.183 --> 00:03:47.686
from the Tooth to Harrenhal
without an escort?

31
00:03:49.854 --> 00:03:52.645
There is a large dragon in
the Riverlands. Your Grace.

32
00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:55.981
- My brother's army is strong. but it does seem...
- I am the prince regent.

33
00:03:55.985 --> 00:03:58.734
not a dog to be called to heel.

34
00:03:58.738 --> 00:04:01.028
Tell your brother that if
he does not deliver his host

35
00:04:01.032 --> 00:04:03.322
to Harrenhal. "with haste."

36
00:04:03.326 --> 00:04:05.866
Daemon's dragon will become
the least of his worries.

37
00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:07.743
Your irritations are
justified. Aemond.

38
00:04:07.747 --> 00:04:09.704
- but it does seem...
- Aemond Targaryen: I have a task for you

39
00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:12.210
as well. Ser Tyland.

40
00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:15.880
(birds chirping)

41
00:04:18.299 --> 00:04:20.427
We will make an alliance
with the Triarchy.

42
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:24.218
I've had enough of
this cursed blockade.

43
00:04:24.222 --> 00:04:28.347
My prince... you cannot mean
to treat with the Free Cities.

44
00:04:28.351 --> 00:04:31.225
The captains of their ships
are dangerous mercenaries.

45
00:04:31.229 --> 00:04:33.394
- little more than pirates...
- They are a stone's throw away

46
00:04:33.398 --> 00:04:35.066
across the Narrow Sea.

47
00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:38.862
Lannister and Hightower ships
will take months to arrive.

48
00:04:39.654 --> 00:04:44.030
The Triarchy will delight in the chance
to terrorize the Sea Snake again.

49
00:04:44.034 --> 00:04:46.365
Let them weaken his blockade

50
00:04:46.369 --> 00:04:49.247
while our true allies make
their long journey east.

51
00:04:49.956 --> 00:04:52.538
The Triarchy may play
at accepting terms.

52
00:04:52.542 --> 00:04:53.873
but they are not to be trusted.

53
00:04:53.877 --> 00:04:56.625
Your father knew this.

54
00:04:56.629 --> 00:04:58.294
What has come of our
letters to the Greyjoys?

55
00:04:58.298 --> 00:05:00.588
They have been to no avail.

56
00:05:00.592 --> 00:05:02.757
The Red Kraken waits.

57
00:05:02.761 --> 00:05:04.425
seeking his best advantage.

58
00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:08.262
Though we may draw him in
with honey. if it comes to it.

59
00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:09.722
An offer of marriage. perhaps.

60
00:05:09.726 --> 00:05:11.102
to the dowager queen?

61
00:05:11.936 --> 00:05:13.605
Out of the question.

62
00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:16.729
Alas.

63
00:05:16.733 --> 00:05:19.774
The dowager queen speaks
wisely. Your Grace.

64
00:05:19.778 --> 00:05:21.275
Even if the blockade
could be broken.

65
00:05:21.279 --> 00:05:23.736
are we to invite these alien
raiders into our waters.

66
00:05:23.740 --> 00:05:25.905
so close to King's Landing?

67
00:05:25.909 --> 00:05:28.953
It's time you set out
for Harrenhal. I think.

68
00:05:31.539 --> 00:05:33.579
Your Grace. if Daemon
prevails in the Riverlands.

69
00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:35.794
I no longer have the
numbers to challenge him.

70
00:05:37.504 --> 00:05:39.168
We lost much at Rook's Rest.

71
00:05:39.172 --> 00:05:40.965
as you well know.

72
00:05:43.677 --> 00:05:47.593
The longer we wait. the
more chance he will prevail.

73
00:05:47.597 --> 00:05:50.137
Lannister will
march from the west.

74
00:05:50.141 --> 00:05:52.181
Take what strength we
have and force Daemon

75
00:05:52.185 --> 00:05:55.601
- and his Riverlords to fight on two fronts.
- His Grace speaks wisely.

76
00:05:55.605 --> 00:05:57.770
Criston Cole: We would do better
to await the Hightower host

77
00:05:57.774 --> 00:05:59.980
- and set out in good time.
- Aemond: There is no time.

78
00:05:59.984 --> 00:06:02.024
It's a fortnight's
march to Harrenhal.

79
00:06:02.028 --> 00:06:03.984
We must strike before
his army is raised.

80
00:06:03.988 --> 00:06:06.320
Criston: And you yourself?

81
00:06:06.324 --> 00:06:08.993
I will fly out to meet
you when the time is ripe.

82
00:06:09.911 --> 00:06:12.330
My uncle is a
challenge I welcome...

83
00:06:13.373 --> 00:06:14.791
if he dares face me.

84
00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:21.256
I see we're all agreed.

85
00:06:26.845 --> 00:06:28.096
Your Grace.

86
00:06:31.558 --> 00:06:33.180
(door opens)

87
00:06:33.184 --> 00:06:34.561
Mother...

88
00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:37.522
a word.

89
00:06:37.897 --> 00:06:39.899
(distant chatter)

90
00:06:43.069 --> 00:06:44.316
(door closes)

91
00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:46.360
I caution you. Aemond.

92
00:06:46.364 --> 00:06:48.654
- boldness is one thing. but overconfidence...
- Remind me of your place

93
00:06:48.658 --> 00:06:50.535
on the small council.

94
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:53.743
You know very well I represented

95
00:06:53.747 --> 00:06:55.327
your father during the
last years of his life.

96
00:06:55.331 --> 00:06:58.460
- and I have been a councilor to Aegon.
- Capably so.

97
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:01.046
My father's dead

98
00:07:01.796 --> 00:07:03.214
and Aegon is...

99
00:07:04.758 --> 00:07:05.884
Mm.

100
00:07:09.637 --> 00:07:11.431
You served the realm well...

101
00:07:12.390 --> 00:07:14.059
at a time of need.

102
00:07:15.894 --> 00:07:19.064
That need is ended. You
are no longer obliged.

103
00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:21.354
It's not a matter of obligation.

104
00:07:21.358 --> 00:07:22.772
This council has need
of a tempering voice.

105
00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:24.774
We have more than enough
of those. if you ask me.

106
00:07:24.778 --> 00:07:27.360
You have the
impetuousness of youth...

107
00:07:27.364 --> 00:07:28.527
and its arrogance.

108
00:07:28.531 --> 00:07:29.737
neither of which is to
be desired in a king.

109
00:07:29.741 --> 00:07:31.364
I release you of your seat.

110
00:07:31.368 --> 00:07:32.827
such as it was.

111
00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:36.247
I'm sure you'll be much
pleased to return to more...

112
00:07:37.499 --> 00:07:39.125
domestic pursuits.

113
00:07:46.925 --> 00:07:48.927
(birds chirping)

114
00:07:50.804 --> 00:07:52.426
Have the indignities
of your childhood

115
00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:54.015
not yet sufficiently
been avenged?

116
00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:14.452
You have the gratitude
of the crown.

117
00:08:16.788 --> 00:08:18.540
(breathing heavily)

118
00:08:28.466 --> 00:08:31.511
(pensive music playing)

119
00:08:46.401 --> 00:08:48.403
(indistinct chatter)

120
00:08:54.868 --> 00:08:56.870
♪

121
00:09:13.428 --> 00:09:15.013
Your Grace.

122
00:09:19.100 --> 00:09:21.349
(music fades out)

123
00:09:21.353 --> 00:09:22.687
Bring him forth.

124
00:09:34.532 --> 00:09:36.951
Guard: Ser Steffon
Darklyn. Your Grace.

125
00:09:40.038 --> 00:09:42.040
Is aught amiss. Your Grace?

126
00:09:42.540 --> 00:09:43.663
My lords.

127
00:09:43.667 --> 00:09:45.873
I find myself. Ser Steffon.

128
00:09:45.877 --> 00:09:48.421
in an impossible position.

129
00:09:49.631 --> 00:09:52.088
(inhales) I have
lost Princess Rhaenys

130
00:09:52.092 --> 00:09:53.673
and her dragon.

131
00:09:53.677 --> 00:09:56.884
I hold an island seat
with no land army.

132
00:09:56.888 --> 00:09:59.887
And I must not go
to battle myself...

133
00:09:59.891 --> 00:10:01.097
as I am constantly told.

134
00:10:01.101 --> 00:10:03.432
lest I am slain or captured.

135
00:10:03.436 --> 00:10:06.731
and... with me. our
hopes of victory.

136
00:10:08.066 --> 00:10:12.570
There is still Daemon and
Caraxes... and the Rivermen.

137
00:10:13.571 --> 00:10:15.407
That remains to be seen.

138
00:10:17.575 --> 00:10:21.746
In any case. I must now
proceed as if I stand alone.

139
00:10:22.914 --> 00:10:24.704
And I see now. that to do that.

140
00:10:24.708 --> 00:10:26.706
I need more dragon riders

141
00:10:26.710 --> 00:10:30.084
for Vermithor and
Silverwing. and for Seasmoke.

142
00:10:30.088 --> 00:10:32.461
who I believe misses his bond.

143
00:10:32.465 --> 00:10:36.257
But there are no more in
your family. Your Grace.

144
00:10:36.261 --> 00:10:38.930
- Your younger sons are babes.
- Rhaenyra Targaryen: Mm.

145
00:10:40.265 --> 00:10:42.267
Mm. there is Princess Rhaena.

146
00:10:42.767 --> 00:10:45.766
She has attempted it. alas.

147
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:48.978
but the dragons here would
not take her as a rider.

148
00:10:48.982 --> 00:10:51.109
- Then who could do it?
- You.

149
00:10:52.694 --> 00:10:53.695
(chuckles)

150
00:10:54.779 --> 00:10:57.278
You are of noble birth.

151
00:10:57.282 --> 00:10:59.447
And I had always
heard. as you know.

152
00:10:59.451 --> 00:11:03.784
that the Darklyns and the
Targaryens had some common blood.

153
00:11:03.788 --> 00:11:07.496
I looked into the history.
and indeed it is true.

154
00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:10.166
Your grandmother's
grandmother. Aeriana.

155
00:11:10.170 --> 00:11:12.501
- was born a Targaryen princess.
- (Bartimos sighs)

156
00:11:12.505 --> 00:11:14.795
And I have been thinking.

157
00:11:14.799 --> 00:11:16.676
could it be possible?

158
00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:20.176
To even consider such a thing.

159
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:21.427
I must protest. Your Grace.

160
00:11:21.431 --> 00:11:23.975
the risk involved
in such a venture...

161
00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:27.808
I am but a man.

162
00:11:27.812 --> 00:11:30.853
The dragons are gods.

163
00:11:30.857 --> 00:11:34.402
Your Grace honors me
beyond what I deserve.

164
00:11:39.491 --> 00:11:44.162
You understand your
peril. Ser Steffon?

165
00:11:44.496 --> 00:11:46.706
I do not compel you to do this.

166
00:11:47.374 --> 00:11:50.706
It has never been
attempted before.

167
00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:54.839
To claim a dragon. you must
also be prepared to die.

168
00:11:55.423 --> 00:11:58.464
I well understand the risk
and I accept it with gladness.

169
00:11:58.468 --> 00:12:01.509
{\an8}I swore to ward my queen
with all my strength.

170
00:12:01.513 --> 00:12:03.181
{\an8}and to give my blood for hers.

171
00:12:04.432 --> 00:12:06.434
That is my oath. Your Grace.

172
00:12:08.687 --> 00:12:10.897
Then perhaps the
gods will favor us.

173
00:12:13.858 --> 00:12:15.860
(unsettling sounds)

174
00:12:34.421 --> 00:12:36.423
(footsteps echoing)

175
00:12:40.719 --> 00:12:42.137
(softly) Brother?

176
00:12:46.891 --> 00:12:50.562
- (ominous sounds)
- (door closes)

177
00:12:53.565 --> 00:12:55.775
Viserys Targaryen
(echoing): Did you say it?

178
00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:59.571
"The Heir for a Day."

179
00:13:00.447 --> 00:13:02.236
Did you say it?

180
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:06.073
(softly) You can't possibly
still be angry about this.

181
00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:09.748
My family was just destroyed.

182
00:13:10.665 --> 00:13:12.917
You should've been at my side.

183
00:13:14.586 --> 00:13:17.585
But instead you chose to
celebrate your own rise.

184
00:13:17.589 --> 00:13:19.295
Laughing at me...

185
00:13:19.299 --> 00:13:22.715
laughing with the
whores and lickspittles.

186
00:13:22.719 --> 00:13:24.550
No.

187
00:13:24.554 --> 00:13:26.598
You have no allies
at court but me.

188
00:13:27.599 --> 00:13:29.559
I have only ever defended you.

189
00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:33.146
And everything I've given you.
you've thrown back in my face!

190
00:13:36.983 --> 00:13:39.607
- I have decided...
- Don't.

191
00:13:39.611 --> 00:13:41.942
...to name a new heir.

192
00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:44.612
You are to return to Runestone

193
00:13:44.616 --> 00:13:46.781
and your lady wife at once.

194
00:13:46.785 --> 00:13:50.284
and you are to do
so without quarrel.

195
00:13:50.288 --> 00:13:53.333
by order of your king.

196
00:13:59.881 --> 00:14:02.884
(Viserys crying quietly)

197
00:14:14.521 --> 00:14:16.519
(door rattles)

198
00:14:16.523 --> 00:14:18.400
(echoes) No!

199
00:14:19.192 --> 00:14:23.154
Open the door!

200
00:14:24.489 --> 00:14:26.491
(high-pitched ringing)

201
00:14:30.495 --> 00:14:32.497
(heavy breathing)

202
00:14:36.084 --> 00:14:38.712
(softly) Open
the door. Please.

203
00:14:41.089 --> 00:14:42.090
Please.

204
00:14:44.509 --> 00:14:45.965
Please. Ah!

205
00:14:45.969 --> 00:14:48.013
(Daemon panting)

206
00:14:51.099 --> 00:14:53.351
May I be of
assistance. Your Grace?

207
00:14:55.353 --> 00:14:57.476
- What are you playing at. old man?
- I do wonder. Your Grace.

208
00:14:57.480 --> 00:14:58.894
if you're getting enough sleep.

209
00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:01.063
- This old place...
- Are you mocking me?

210
00:15:01.067 --> 00:15:02.736
- No.
- Sit!

211
00:15:03.361 --> 00:15:05.359
(Daemon panting)

212
00:15:05.363 --> 00:15:08.487
Or are you perhaps the culprit who
has been tampering with my peace?

213
00:15:08.491 --> 00:15:10.535
A friend by day
and a foe by night.

214
00:15:11.453 --> 00:15:13.159
- To what end?
- To mine. perhaps.

215
00:15:13.163 --> 00:15:14.205
Ah!

216
00:15:15.957 --> 00:15:20.962
Perhaps... you
resent my being here.

217
00:15:22.380 --> 00:15:23.798
Perhaps...

218
00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:27.048
you are an agent

219
00:15:27.052 --> 00:15:30.343
- of the Hightower rabble.
- (Simon whimpering)

220
00:15:30.347 --> 00:15:32.887
Ha. Or are you still in league

221
00:15:32.891 --> 00:15:34.221
with your club-footed nephew?

222
00:15:34.225 --> 00:15:37.433
- Or is it Rhaenyra herself?!
- I assure you...

223
00:15:37.437 --> 00:15:39.393
I assure you. Your Grace.

224
00:15:39.397 --> 00:15:41.232
(laughing)

225
00:15:43.735 --> 00:15:45.320
(shushing)

226
00:15:51.242 --> 00:15:54.367
Whatever your game is. Strong...

227
00:15:54.371 --> 00:15:56.414
I assure you...

228
00:15:57.082 --> 00:16:00.502
- your king is on his guard.
- Yes. Your Grace.

229
00:16:04.798 --> 00:16:06.800
And stop watching me.

230
00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:22.023
(tense music playing)

231
00:16:26.111 --> 00:16:28.113
(Caraxes calls)

232
00:16:35.286 --> 00:16:37.288
♪

233
00:16:41.960 --> 00:16:43.332
You weren't going
to bid me farewell?

234
00:16:43.336 --> 00:16:45.793
There's something wrong with me.

235
00:16:45.797 --> 00:16:49.630
Someone poisoned me.
The food. the wine.

236
00:16:49.634 --> 00:16:51.090
Or else it's this
swamp air. or...

237
00:16:51.094 --> 00:16:52.675
The ghost of Harren the Black

238
00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:54.844
moaning his curses
from Kingspyre Tower.

239
00:16:54.848 --> 00:16:56.804
Drivel! All of it!

240
00:16:56.808 --> 00:16:59.473
The ghosts. the curses.
the blasted weirwood bed!

241
00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:02.810
- I'm done with it!
- Ah. yes. It is your way. is it not?

242
00:17:02.814 --> 00:17:05.108
When something does not
please you. you run.

243
00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:07.648
Dragonstone. the Stepstones.

244
00:17:07.652 --> 00:17:09.150
Pentos. Harrenhal.

245
00:17:09.154 --> 00:17:11.156
I awake and I do not
know where I've been.

246
00:17:12.198 --> 00:17:14.655
There are older
things in this world

247
00:17:14.659 --> 00:17:18.663
than you or I. or living memory.

248
00:17:20.331 --> 00:17:24.377
You are not the player.
but a piece on the board.

249
00:17:25.337 --> 00:17:27.505
As am I. for that matter.

250
00:17:29.716 --> 00:17:31.172
I'm not like you.

251
00:17:31.176 --> 00:17:34.429
- (Caraxes screeches)
- In some ways. no.

252
00:17:35.013 --> 00:17:37.678
You struggle to see there's
an anger that blinds you.

253
00:17:37.682 --> 00:17:39.893
She never even wanted it.

254
00:17:40.685 --> 00:17:43.184
The crown. She
spared it no thought.

255
00:17:43.188 --> 00:17:45.686
Well. that's perhaps why your
brother gave the crown to her.

256
00:17:45.690 --> 00:17:47.730
Perhaps those who strive for it

257
00:17:47.734 --> 00:17:49.023
are the least suited to wear it.

258
00:17:49.027 --> 00:17:50.904
Don't lecture me!

259
00:17:56.576 --> 00:17:59.871
Viserys never wanted it
himself. if you recall.

260
00:18:01.247 --> 00:18:04.038
It came to him. and
he did his best.

261
00:18:04.042 --> 00:18:07.833
It's not a prize to be
won. but a burden to bear.

262
00:18:07.837 --> 00:18:09.881
(Caraxes calling)

263
00:18:20.725 --> 00:18:22.727
(wind blowing)

264
00:18:25.105 --> 00:18:27.228
If you have any counsel for
dealing with the Riverlords.

265
00:18:27.232 --> 00:18:29.067
I'd be glad of it.

266
00:18:34.155 --> 00:18:37.029
Daemon Targaryen
asking for help?

267
00:18:37.033 --> 00:18:38.243
Counsel.

268
00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:41.162
(Caraxes grumbling)

269
00:18:43.289 --> 00:18:46.414
House Tully is not the largest
house in the Riverlands.

270
00:18:46.418 --> 00:18:47.456
nor is it the richest.

271
00:18:47.460 --> 00:18:49.504
but it is the most stable.

272
00:18:50.422 --> 00:18:51.752
The Tullys' wisdom has kept

273
00:18:51.756 --> 00:18:54.046
the river houses in
line for centuries.

274
00:18:54.050 --> 00:18:55.798
They would kill each
other to the last man

275
00:18:55.802 --> 00:18:58.096
- if it were not for their liege lord.
- (chuckles)

276
00:18:58.972 --> 00:19:01.433
That dotard is of no use to us.

277
00:19:02.767 --> 00:19:05.979
But Grover Tully is
their Lord Paramount.

278
00:19:06.604 --> 00:19:09.979
Without him. they will never
raise their banners as one.

279
00:19:09.983 --> 00:19:11.568
Rivermen are made of mud.

280
00:19:12.110 --> 00:19:13.441
They would rather
die stuck in it

281
00:19:13.445 --> 00:19:15.109
than yield one inch
to one another.

282
00:19:15.113 --> 00:19:16.777
Then I can do nothing.

283
00:19:16.781 --> 00:19:19.617
You... no.

284
00:19:21.494 --> 00:19:23.496
(owl screeching)

285
00:19:28.335 --> 00:19:30.170
I need help. Alys.

286
00:19:32.839 --> 00:19:34.466
Do nothing now.

287
00:19:36.051 --> 00:19:38.841
In three days' time.
the winds will shift.

288
00:19:38.845 --> 00:19:40.847
(Caraxes screeching)

289
00:19:47.354 --> 00:19:50.565
(dragon keepers chanting hymn)

290
00:20:13.672 --> 00:20:15.674
(chanting continues)

291
00:20:38.405 --> 00:20:40.403
(hymn concludes)

292
00:20:40.407 --> 00:20:42.075
(muttering softly)

293
00:20:45.537 --> 00:20:47.205
(silence)

294
00:20:57.382 --> 00:20:59.384
(unsettling sounds)

295
00:21:00.552 --> 00:21:02.721
(wind blowing)

296
00:21:03.763 --> 00:21:05.765
(dragon grumbling)

297
00:21:06.474 --> 00:21:08.889
(heavy footsteps)

298
00:21:08.893 --> 00:21:11.100
(dragon screeches)

299
00:21:11.104 --> 00:21:14.149
(tense music playing)

300
00:21:15.567 --> 00:21:17.944
(dragon keepers
shouting commands)

301
00:21:18.486 --> 00:21:20.113
(roars)

302
00:21:22.073 --> 00:21:24.075
♪

303
00:21:27.996 --> 00:21:29.914
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

304
00:21:31.833 --> 00:21:32.834
Gods.

305
00:21:34.753 --> 00:21:36.588
{\an8}(dragon keeper
speaks High Valyrian)

306
00:21:37.756 --> 00:21:39.341
(grumbles)

307
00:21:42.969 --> 00:21:44.596
Seasmoke...

308
00:21:46.514 --> 00:21:47.720
<i>Dohaeras.</i>

309
00:21:47.724 --> 00:21:49.972
(Seasmoke screeches)

310
00:21:49.976 --> 00:21:52.312
{\an8}(dragon keeper
speaks High Valyrian)

311
00:21:56.524 --> 00:21:58.147
♪

312
00:21:58.151 --> 00:22:00.195
Dragon keeper:
Do not show fear.

313
00:22:01.279 --> 00:22:02.614
<i>Rybas!</i>

314
00:22:05.700 --> 00:22:07.619
{\an8}(speaks High Valyrian)

315
00:22:13.667 --> 00:22:15.915
(music fades out)

316
00:22:15.919 --> 00:22:17.545
(grumbling)

317
00:22:20.382 --> 00:22:21.800
(exhales)

318
00:22:34.312 --> 00:22:37.524
(light. suspenseful
music playing)

319
00:23:01.881 --> 00:23:03.883
♪

320
00:23:06.094 --> 00:23:08.096
(Seasmoke screeches)

321
00:23:11.850 --> 00:23:13.852
♪

322
00:23:18.857 --> 00:23:20.233
I've done it.

323
00:23:23.194 --> 00:23:24.316
{\an8}(screeches)

324
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:26.281
{\an8}(dragon keeper
speaks High Valyrian)

325
00:23:27.699 --> 00:23:29.697
{\an8}- (screeches)
- No.

326
00:23:29.701 --> 00:23:32.370
(dragon keepers.
Steffon yelling)

327
00:23:33.204 --> 00:23:35.874
(dramatic music playing)

328
00:23:38.293 --> 00:23:39.878
(Seasmoke screeches)

329
00:23:42.464 --> 00:23:44.712
(shouts in High Valyrian)

330
00:23:44.716 --> 00:23:46.718
(agonized shouting)

331
00:23:49.888 --> 00:23:51.052
Mother!

332
00:23:51.056 --> 00:23:53.099
♪

333
00:23:57.228 --> 00:24:00.353
{\an8}worker: Up. up. up!

334
00:24:00.357 --> 00:24:02.400
(indistinct chatter)

335
00:24:03.401 --> 00:24:05.441
Corlys Velaryon: Alyn!

336
00:24:05.445 --> 00:24:06.905
Alyn of Hull: M'lord.

337
00:24:08.740 --> 00:24:10.450
Corlys: I'm pleased
with our progress.

338
00:24:10.909 --> 00:24:13.328
This ship will sail
in a few days' time.

339
00:24:14.079 --> 00:24:15.534
The blockade is sure
to be challenged.

340
00:24:15.538 --> 00:24:17.078
be it by Lions or Krakens.

341
00:24:17.082 --> 00:24:19.872
Your men will be glad
to have you among 'em.

342
00:24:19.876 --> 00:24:21.419
I wish you to sail with me.

343
00:24:22.671 --> 00:24:25.127
As my first mate.

344
00:24:25.131 --> 00:24:27.421
I'm grateful for
the offer. m'lord...

345
00:24:27.425 --> 00:24:29.215
- but...
- We will set course for Sharp Point.

346
00:24:29.219 --> 00:24:32.968
Lord Bar Emmon wishes to send
his nephew aboard as a boatswain.

347
00:24:32.972 --> 00:24:35.642
There are more experienced
men at your service.

348
00:24:37.435 --> 00:24:39.308
I was younger than you

349
00:24:39.312 --> 00:24:41.398
when I took my first command.

350
00:24:42.273 --> 00:24:44.605
You distinguished yourself
in the Stepstones.

351
00:24:44.609 --> 00:24:46.820
and you have the
respect of the crew.

352
00:24:48.363 --> 00:24:50.990
You are a fine
choice for this post.

353
00:24:53.993 --> 00:24:56.287
Is this an order or a request?

354
00:24:58.456 --> 00:25:00.621
(chuckles) I will
expect you to report

355
00:25:00.625 --> 00:25:03.211
for your duties on the morrow.

356
00:25:04.796 --> 00:25:06.464
As my lordship commands.

357
00:25:09.801 --> 00:25:11.803
(indistinct chatter)

358
00:25:18.518 --> 00:25:20.520
(quiet chatter)

359
00:25:29.029 --> 00:25:31.152
- Bit thin. isn't it?
- Dyana: It's either that or the fish.

360
00:25:31.156 --> 00:25:33.575
Nothing but fish
in this damn city.

361
00:25:36.536 --> 00:25:38.163
Patron: An ale here.

362
00:25:39.998 --> 00:25:41.829
Dyana: Aught to eat with it?

363
00:25:41.833 --> 00:25:43.998
Patron: Don't think I
can stomach it. lass.

364
00:25:44.002 --> 00:25:46.671
Yeah. you've made the right
choice there. I'll tell you that.

365
00:25:49.341 --> 00:25:51.130
Makes you sick. doesn't it?

366
00:25:51.134 --> 00:25:54.508
Knowing they're banqueting
every night at the castle.

367
00:25:54.512 --> 00:25:57.011
- while we go without.
- Dyana: That can't be true.

368
00:25:57.015 --> 00:26:00.848
Madam Sylvi: My girls were taken
to the Red Keep a few nights ago.

369
00:26:00.852 --> 00:26:04.977
Feasting and merriment
for the new Prince Regent.

370
00:26:04.981 --> 00:26:07.646
Dyana (hushed): No! And him
always acting so correct.

371
00:26:07.650 --> 00:26:09.694
Sylvi: I'll tell you.
he's no penny pincher.

372
00:26:10.236 --> 00:26:14.070
- They were well-paid. and well-fed too.
- Dyana: Hm.

373
00:26:14.074 --> 00:26:16.697
On what? Fish with
more fish on the side?

374
00:26:16.701 --> 00:26:19.033
Racks of lamb. my love.

375
00:26:19.037 --> 00:26:22.370
Mince pies. honey cakes.

376
00:26:22.374 --> 00:26:24.705
beef and gravy.

377
00:26:24.709 --> 00:26:26.207
And what do you think?

378
00:26:26.211 --> 00:26:29.710
There is to be another revel
on the morrow with dancing.

379
00:26:29.714 --> 00:26:31.132
That ain't right.

380
00:26:31.925 --> 00:26:33.927
Apologies. my good man.

381
00:26:35.553 --> 00:26:37.718
I should not have
spoken so free.

382
00:26:37.722 --> 00:26:39.387
The royals would
never countenance me

383
00:26:39.391 --> 00:26:42.644
speaking about their
bounty. even if it's true.

384
00:26:43.728 --> 00:26:47.561
King Viserys loved his
feasts and his wine.

385
00:26:47.565 --> 00:26:50.398
but never while our
smallfolk went without.

386
00:26:50.402 --> 00:26:53.405
Mm. aye. But he's gone now...

387
00:26:54.823 --> 00:26:57.784
and his rightful
heir denied her seat.

388
00:27:02.747 --> 00:27:06.751
Well... no use wondering
what might have been.

389
00:27:20.807 --> 00:27:22.763
(muffled speaking)

390
00:27:22.767 --> 00:27:24.473
Bartimos Celtigar: ...I am far
from alone among your councilors

391
00:27:24.477 --> 00:27:26.726
in holding this to be a truly
unfortunate result. Your Grace.

392
00:27:26.730 --> 00:27:28.728
Seasmoke has fled Dragonstone.

393
00:27:28.732 --> 00:27:31.230
and Ser Steffon was
a valiant knight.

394
00:27:31.234 --> 00:27:32.940
Most regrettable.

395
00:27:32.944 --> 00:27:35.317
if. perhaps. foreseeable.

396
00:27:35.321 --> 00:27:36.902
I myself. if you recall.

397
00:27:36.906 --> 00:27:38.946
was in favor of treating
with Lord Mooton

398
00:27:38.950 --> 00:27:40.114
to march on Rook's Rest.

399
00:27:40.118 --> 00:27:41.741
A more conventional approach.

400
00:27:41.745 --> 00:27:45.161
true. not as sensational.

401
00:27:45.165 --> 00:27:47.580
And. uh. his... his
numbers were few.

402
00:27:47.584 --> 00:27:49.794
but we may yet retake...

403
00:27:52.505 --> 00:27:55.717
It is my fault. I think. that
you have forgotten to fear me.

404
00:27:56.634 --> 00:27:59.637
(tense music playing)

405
00:28:05.518 --> 00:28:07.520
♪

406
00:28:30.919 --> 00:28:32.921
♪

407
00:28:36.716 --> 00:28:39.215
Mysaria: It was worth the
risk. no matter the outcome.

408
00:28:39.219 --> 00:28:41.346
More good men killed?

409
00:28:41.930 --> 00:28:44.303
- That's my fault.
- Ser Steffon went willingly.

410
00:28:44.307 --> 00:28:46.681
It was a reckless thought.

411
00:28:46.685 --> 00:28:48.140
That an ancient Valyrian beast

412
00:28:48.144 --> 00:28:49.684
would suffer a
Darklyn to ride it.

413
00:28:49.688 --> 00:28:52.019
Surely he was not
the only possibility.

414
00:28:52.023 --> 00:28:53.312
Might there not be others

415
00:28:53.316 --> 00:28:54.730
among the highborn of
the Seven Kingdoms?

416
00:28:54.734 --> 00:28:56.649
And who will be so
foolish as to try.

417
00:28:56.653 --> 00:28:58.613
after hearing what
befell Ser Steffon?

418
00:29:00.907 --> 00:29:03.118
(nearby dragon grumbles)

419
00:29:05.203 --> 00:29:06.788
I will look again.

420
00:29:08.039 --> 00:29:10.997
But Darklyn had the
most likely claim.

421
00:29:11.001 --> 00:29:12.999
There is good news to be had.

422
00:29:13.003 --> 00:29:15.710
The smallfolk of King's
Landing are listening.

423
00:29:15.714 --> 00:29:17.586
They were ready enough to hear.

424
00:29:17.590 --> 00:29:19.547
The usurpers have
abandoned them.

425
00:29:19.551 --> 00:29:22.762
They are hungry. and they
need someone to blame.

426
00:29:24.222 --> 00:29:25.386
Will it be enough?

427
00:29:25.390 --> 00:29:26.887
We have laid the kindling only.

428
00:29:26.891 --> 00:29:28.681
Tonight we will light it.

429
00:29:28.685 --> 00:29:30.099
and watch it begin to flare.

430
00:29:30.103 --> 00:29:32.226
And when it does. Aemond
will put it down with force.

431
00:29:32.230 --> 00:29:33.898
That will make it
rise the hotter.

432
00:29:34.315 --> 00:29:36.605
He cannot destroy his own city.

433
00:29:36.609 --> 00:29:38.024
Neither can they overthrow him.

434
00:29:38.028 --> 00:29:41.277
Maybe not. but it is
harder to wage war abroad

435
00:29:41.281 --> 00:29:44.159
when you must also
keep peace at home.

436
00:29:45.910 --> 00:29:47.912
Then let us see to our plan.

437
00:29:53.001 --> 00:29:55.003
If I may. Your Grace...

438
00:29:56.421 --> 00:29:58.965
this becomes you.

439
00:30:02.927 --> 00:30:05.597
(pensive music playing)

440
00:30:07.474 --> 00:30:09.472
(street chatter)

441
00:30:09.476 --> 00:30:11.519
(dog barking)

442
00:30:16.149 --> 00:30:18.606
- That's the last one.
- Thank you.

443
00:30:18.610 --> 00:30:21.446
- What? They haven't run out. have they?
- Nothing.

444
00:30:22.322 --> 00:30:23.986
There ain't nothing left.

445
00:30:23.990 --> 00:30:27.535
I've been waiting all day.
I'll take anything. Scraps?

446
00:30:28.495 --> 00:30:30.493
(horse neighs)

447
00:30:30.497 --> 00:30:32.578
(sheep bleating)

448
00:30:32.582 --> 00:30:35.794
(light. tense music playing)

449
00:30:37.295 --> 00:30:40.628
Got enough sheep for your
dragons then. but none for us.

450
00:30:40.632 --> 00:30:43.631
Where's our meat?
We want meat!

451
00:30:43.635 --> 00:30:45.679
(smallfolk shouting)

452
00:30:48.014 --> 00:30:49.637
Jasper "Ironrod" Wylde:
<i>It seems. Your Grace.</i>

453
00:30:49.641 --> 00:30:52.306
<i>that the smallfolk
have become restless.</i>

454
00:30:52.310 --> 00:30:53.808
Aemond: So?

455
00:30:53.812 --> 00:30:56.435
Ironrod: There is not
food enough in the city.

456
00:30:56.439 --> 00:30:59.313
Those with means have bought
more than their share.

457
00:30:59.317 --> 00:31:02.108
All the more reason Ser Tyland
must break the blockade.

458
00:31:02.112 --> 00:31:04.652
In the meantime. the
people are hungry.

459
00:31:04.656 --> 00:31:06.574
and their anger is rising.

460
00:31:07.867 --> 00:31:09.699
The enemy without may
be fought with swords.

461
00:31:09.703 --> 00:31:12.118
The enemy within
is more insidious.

462
00:31:12.122 --> 00:31:14.662
Why is this anger
directed at us?

463
00:31:14.666 --> 00:31:15.830
It is Rhaenyra the Pretender

464
00:31:15.834 --> 00:31:16.998
who ordered the Gullet closed

465
00:31:17.002 --> 00:31:18.833
and left them all to starve.

466
00:31:18.837 --> 00:31:20.839
They still look to you to
ensure their well-being.

467
00:31:22.340 --> 00:31:23.925
That is the burden of authority.

468
00:31:25.051 --> 00:31:27.053
But you should not go it alone.

469
00:31:28.513 --> 00:31:31.850
It does occur to me that Your
Grace has yet to name a Hand.

470
00:31:32.600 --> 00:31:34.515
Ser Criston. of course.
served your brother.

471
00:31:34.519 --> 00:31:37.355
but you need one who may
advance your cause...

472
00:31:37.939 --> 00:31:39.274
with shrewdness and subtlety.

473
00:31:41.276 --> 00:31:43.111
Do you take me for a fool?

474
00:31:46.698 --> 00:31:48.571
- On the contrary. my prince.
- Aemond: I've little patience

475
00:31:48.575 --> 00:31:50.656
for the self-important.
Lord Larys.

476
00:31:50.660 --> 00:31:53.288
and even less for
flatterers and lickspittles.

477
00:31:54.622 --> 00:31:56.249
But you are. as it
happens. correct.

478
00:31:57.208 --> 00:31:58.793
Every king needs a Hand.

479
00:32:00.628 --> 00:32:02.047
I'll make it your
responsibility.

480
00:32:04.549 --> 00:32:07.214
(clears throat) My prince. it
is an honor I'd never considered

481
00:32:07.218 --> 00:32:10.343
- for myself.
- No. not to serve as Hand. you toad.

482
00:32:10.347 --> 00:32:13.512
To fetch him. Send
word to Otto Hightower.

483
00:32:13.516 --> 00:32:15.222
My grandsire may
be overcautious.

484
00:32:15.226 --> 00:32:18.438
but his devotion to his family
has never been in doubt.

485
00:32:19.731 --> 00:32:21.437
Mm. you'll see it done.

486
00:32:21.441 --> 00:32:23.064
(whispers) Your Grace.

487
00:32:23.068 --> 00:32:25.107
- (door closes)
- You're late.

488
00:32:25.111 --> 00:32:28.569
I am happy to report
that His Grace the king

489
00:32:28.573 --> 00:32:30.905
has regained consciousness
this morning.

490
00:32:30.909 --> 00:32:32.573
if only for a few moments.

491
00:32:32.577 --> 00:32:34.617
Ironrod: You said
there was little hope.

492
00:32:34.621 --> 00:32:36.744
Grand Maester Orwyle: He
is stronger than I thought.

493
00:32:36.748 --> 00:32:39.121
This morning his
breath comes easier.

494
00:32:39.125 --> 00:32:42.249
He may yet live. thank the gods.

495
00:32:42.253 --> 00:32:44.130
What happy news.

496
00:32:48.093 --> 00:32:50.095
(Aegon whimpering)

497
00:32:55.308 --> 00:32:56.931
(groaning)

498
00:32:56.935 --> 00:33:00.188
- (labored breathing)
- (door opens)

499
00:33:02.148 --> 00:33:03.441
Aemond: I'll see my brother.

500
00:33:04.651 --> 00:33:05.860
Alone.

501
00:33:06.945 --> 00:33:08.947
(Aegon groaning)

502
00:33:11.157 --> 00:33:13.159
(bell tolling)

503
00:33:13.868 --> 00:33:15.870
(shallow breathing)

504
00:33:19.624 --> 00:33:21.626
(panicked groaning)

505
00:33:22.961 --> 00:33:24.629
(shushing)

506
00:33:28.299 --> 00:33:29.801
What do you remember?

507
00:33:35.306 --> 00:33:36.683
(hoarsely) Nothing.

508
00:33:42.355 --> 00:33:43.982
(grunting)

509
00:33:50.572 --> 00:33:52.574
You challenged Meleys.

510
00:33:54.576 --> 00:33:56.202
It was foolish.

511
00:33:59.330 --> 00:34:02.334
I remember... nothing.

512
00:34:07.672 --> 00:34:09.257
{\an8}(groaning)

513
00:34:11.259 --> 00:34:13.011
(door opens)

514
00:34:16.181 --> 00:34:20.185
- My prince?
- You're in the most capable hands. Your Grace.

515
00:34:28.026 --> 00:34:31.613
It seems my brother has a long
recovery ahead of him. Grand Maester.

516
00:34:34.074 --> 00:34:36.910
See that he is made
to rest comfortably.

517
00:34:42.207 --> 00:34:44.664
Rhaena Targaryen: <i>And I've
decided there is nothing</i>

518
00:34:44.668 --> 00:34:46.419
<i>to be gained with fretfulness.</i>

519
00:34:47.212 --> 00:34:51.549
Not all of us. I suppose.
are called to great deeds.

520
00:34:53.551 --> 00:34:55.804
Some of us must serve
in smaller ways...

521
00:34:56.888 --> 00:35:00.058
even if they are not what we
would choose for ourselves.

522
00:35:01.101 --> 00:35:03.933
(sighs) Meaning no offense. hm?

523
00:35:03.937 --> 00:35:05.980
None of this is your fault.

524
00:35:06.773 --> 00:35:08.396
(Rhaena sighs)

525
00:35:08.400 --> 00:35:10.068
I want Mother.

526
00:35:11.444 --> 00:35:14.447
Yes... well...

527
00:35:15.740 --> 00:35:18.447
I know it's difficult. but...

528
00:35:18.451 --> 00:35:20.495
(sheep bleating)

529
00:35:21.413 --> 00:35:24.416
(unsettling music playing)

530
00:35:39.014 --> 00:35:41.053
(dragon screeches)

531
00:35:41.057 --> 00:35:43.101
♪

532
00:35:45.311 --> 00:35:46.938
(screeches)

533
00:35:53.445 --> 00:35:56.448
- (footsteps approach)
- (music fades out)

534
00:35:58.700 --> 00:36:01.240
Jeyne Arryn: I bring
good news. Rhaena.

535
00:36:01.244 --> 00:36:03.617
Prince Reggio has
answered your letter.

536
00:36:03.621 --> 00:36:05.953
He'll be most pleased
to shelter Rhaenyra's

537
00:36:05.957 --> 00:36:08.043
youngest sons in Pentos.

538
00:36:09.127 --> 00:36:11.296
And their half-sister.

539
00:36:12.881 --> 00:36:14.507
(Jeyne chuckles)

540
00:36:15.216 --> 00:36:17.218
Thought you'd be happy.

541
00:36:18.803 --> 00:36:20.843
Or at least less morose.

542
00:36:20.847 --> 00:36:24.142
- (Rhaena chuckles slightly)
- You hate it here.

543
00:36:26.644 --> 00:36:28.646
You misled me. my lady.

544
00:36:30.982 --> 00:36:32.192
I did what?

545
00:36:34.319 --> 00:36:37.155
There is a large
dragon in the Vale.

546
00:36:39.699 --> 00:36:41.697
(dragon screeches)

547
00:36:41.701 --> 00:36:44.746
Rumor of it began
shortly after the war.

548
00:36:45.246 --> 00:36:48.037
Ranging more broadly for food...

549
00:36:48.041 --> 00:36:50.085
my maesters surmise.

550
00:36:54.214 --> 00:36:59.886
It is large and
formidable. but alas. wild.

551
00:37:01.346 --> 00:37:02.681
Alas.

552
00:37:05.016 --> 00:37:07.348
A merchant cog. the <i>Gay Abandon.</i>

553
00:37:07.352 --> 00:37:09.187
will take you to Pentos.

554
00:37:11.731 --> 00:37:14.146
I'll send six good men to
protect you on the crossing.

555
00:37:14.150 --> 00:37:16.194
(dragon screeches)

556
00:37:18.405 --> 00:37:21.404
- (birds cawing)
- (bell ringing)

557
00:37:21.408 --> 00:37:23.451
(indistinct chatter)

558
00:37:25.620 --> 00:37:28.248
You know you're
not fooling anyone.

559
00:37:30.375 --> 00:37:33.874
Lord Corlys has
chosen to raise you up

560
00:37:33.878 --> 00:37:35.547
to serve alongside him

561
00:37:36.214 --> 00:37:39.843
and yet. you still
continue this subterfuge.

562
00:37:40.385 --> 00:37:42.508
Don't want my men to
get the wrong idea.

563
00:37:42.512 --> 00:37:43.722
About what?

564
00:37:48.018 --> 00:37:50.891
- You're just like him.
- (laughs)

565
00:37:50.895 --> 00:37:52.727
Oh. you make an art
of provoking me.

566
00:37:52.731 --> 00:37:54.895
Addam of Hull: You
saved his life. brother.

567
00:37:54.899 --> 00:37:57.152
Do you never think about
what could be ours?

568
00:37:58.069 --> 00:37:59.904
Or yours. anyway.

569
00:38:00.989 --> 00:38:04.576
The riches... servants...

570
00:38:05.744 --> 00:38:07.033
the Driftwood Throne.

571
00:38:07.037 --> 00:38:08.409
We spent the whole of our lives

572
00:38:08.413 --> 00:38:11.620
in the shadow of the Sea
Snake's great castle.

573
00:38:11.624 --> 00:38:13.873
I do not wish to dwell
in it any longer.

574
00:38:13.877 --> 00:38:17.130
Hm. and so you belittle
your great opportunity.

575
00:38:17.922 --> 00:38:21.926
While me (sucks
teeth) he ignores...

576
00:38:22.677 --> 00:38:24.596
as he always has.

577
00:38:26.765 --> 00:38:29.138
The Sea Snake would
sooner have High Tide

578
00:38:29.142 --> 00:38:32.437
claimed by the sea
than call us his sons.

579
00:38:34.272 --> 00:38:37.938
Stop wasting your life waiting
for something that'll never come.

580
00:38:37.942 --> 00:38:40.945
- (bell ringing)
- (outside chatter)

581
00:38:45.283 --> 00:38:47.285
(birds cawing)

582
00:38:53.875 --> 00:38:56.878
- (wind blowing)
- (footsteps)

583
00:39:03.134 --> 00:39:04.965
It was a bold attempt.

584
00:39:04.969 --> 00:39:07.180
I admire you for it.

585
00:39:11.142 --> 00:39:13.770
They say you struck
Lord Bartimos today

586
00:39:14.354 --> 00:39:16.356
in view of the staff and guard.

587
00:39:17.691 --> 00:39:19.693
The household is abuzz with it.

588
00:39:21.486 --> 00:39:24.318
He's lucky I did
not have his tongue.

589
00:39:24.322 --> 00:39:27.530
And what did he say that was so

590
00:39:27.534 --> 00:39:29.202
deserving?

591
00:39:32.080 --> 00:39:34.499
I have tired of
being protected...

592
00:39:35.000 --> 00:39:36.167
Jace.

593
00:39:39.504 --> 00:39:41.836
I bring to mind too
much their mothers

594
00:39:41.840 --> 00:39:43.508
or their daughters.

595
00:39:44.426 --> 00:39:46.716
They must see in me a ruler.

596
00:39:46.720 --> 00:39:49.135
And the symbols of authority
are not jewels and gowns.

597
00:39:49.139 --> 00:39:50.678
but the shield and the sword.

598
00:39:50.682 --> 00:39:53.639
My ruler is my mother.

599
00:39:53.643 --> 00:39:56.062
And I do not wish it otherwise.

600
00:39:58.773 --> 00:40:00.646
Will you lead us
to war yourself?

601
00:40:00.650 --> 00:40:02.189
Well. for a certainty
I cannot remain here.

602
00:40:02.193 --> 00:40:04.734
pacing the floors. waiting for
defeat and despair to visit me.

603
00:40:04.738 --> 00:40:07.361
- Oh. don't be ridiculous.
- I'm doing all I can.

604
00:40:07.365 --> 00:40:09.697
I have directed Lord Mooton
to march on Rook's Rest.

605
00:40:09.701 --> 00:40:11.490
and sent another raven to
the Vale to persuade...

606
00:40:11.494 --> 00:40:13.659
We may marshal the
strength of the Vale.

607
00:40:13.663 --> 00:40:16.416
Maidenpool. and all
our allies besides.

608
00:40:16.916 --> 00:40:20.128
We will still never match the
strength of the Green armies.

609
00:40:21.713 --> 00:40:24.879
We need Daemon and his dragon.

610
00:40:24.883 --> 00:40:26.380
May I be free for even one hour

611
00:40:26.384 --> 00:40:28.674
of the constant refrain of
Daemon. Daemon. Daemon...

612
00:40:28.678 --> 00:40:30.096
Lorent Marbrand: Your Grace.

613
00:40:30.972 --> 00:40:32.599
The lady Mysaria.

614
00:40:34.601 --> 00:40:37.812
My queen. our gift is sent.

615
00:40:41.566 --> 00:40:42.984
What gift?

616
00:40:44.235 --> 00:40:46.613
Let us hope for clouds over
the Blackwater tonight.

617
00:40:48.656 --> 00:40:51.910
(light. tense music playing)

618
00:41:11.304 --> 00:41:13.306
(wind blowing)

619
00:41:16.935 --> 00:41:18.937
(music intensifies)

620
00:41:24.609 --> 00:41:26.611
(birds cawing)

621
00:41:38.498 --> 00:41:40.500
(music softens)

622
00:41:50.802 --> 00:41:52.804
♪

623
00:42:14.701 --> 00:42:16.703
♪

624
00:42:38.892 --> 00:42:42.520
(music intensifies)

625
00:42:50.403 --> 00:42:52.614
(music fades out)

626
00:42:53.865 --> 00:42:56.034
- (sighs)
- (birds cawing)

627
00:42:57.202 --> 00:42:59.408
(Aegon snoring lightly)

628
00:42:59.412 --> 00:43:01.456
(door opens)

629
00:43:02.415 --> 00:43:04.042
(footsteps approach)

630
00:43:08.213 --> 00:43:09.714
You said he'd improved.

631
00:43:11.883 --> 00:43:15.428
His Grace sleeps nine
hours of every 10...

632
00:43:16.096 --> 00:43:20.054
but he did open his eyes
and speak. however briefly.

633
00:43:20.058 --> 00:43:22.556
His mending may be
long and painful.

634
00:43:22.560 --> 00:43:24.558
but it is my sincere hope

635
00:43:24.562 --> 00:43:27.228
that His Grace will be spared.

636
00:43:27.232 --> 00:43:29.234
And what will he be if he lives?

637
00:43:31.403 --> 00:43:33.405
(birds chirping)

638
00:43:38.618 --> 00:43:42.080
My letters (sniffles)
to my father...

639
00:43:44.082 --> 00:43:49.250
I have sent ravens. again.
to Highgarden and to Oldtown.

640
00:43:49.254 --> 00:43:52.586
And now. to all the great
houses in the Reach.

641
00:43:52.590 --> 00:43:54.922
There has been no
word from Ser Otto.

642
00:43:54.926 --> 00:43:56.428
as of yet.

643
00:44:01.933 --> 00:44:05.099
There is war in the
Reach now. Your Grace.

644
00:44:05.103 --> 00:44:09.061
House Beesbury has raised arms
against the Hightower host.

645
00:44:09.065 --> 00:44:12.610
Retribution for
their lord's demise.

646
00:44:35.133 --> 00:44:37.135
(Alicent sniffles)

647
00:44:40.513 --> 00:44:42.140
(crying) I'm sorry.

648
00:44:43.641 --> 00:44:44.805
I'm sorry.

649
00:44:44.809 --> 00:44:46.853
(deep breath)

650
00:44:52.650 --> 00:44:54.652
(birds chirping)

651
00:44:59.366 --> 00:45:01.368
(deep breath)

652
00:45:07.332 --> 00:45:09.334
(indistinct chatter)

653
00:45:10.251 --> 00:45:12.253
(horses neighing)

654
00:45:24.849 --> 00:45:26.555
Gwayne Hightower: Sister.

655
00:45:26.559 --> 00:45:27.852
Gwayne.

656
00:45:29.437 --> 00:45:31.439
'Tis well that I found you.

657
00:45:32.357 --> 00:45:34.359
I wish to give you my blessing.

658
00:45:34.943 --> 00:45:36.857
Well...

659
00:45:36.861 --> 00:45:39.531
my thanks to the queen dowager.

660
00:45:45.078 --> 00:45:47.702
I wondered if you've
heard from father?

661
00:45:47.706 --> 00:45:49.745
I've sent ravens to
Highgarden and Oldtown.

662
00:45:49.749 --> 00:45:51.664
but have had no reply.

663
00:45:51.668 --> 00:45:53.708
I've heard nothing

664
00:45:53.712 --> 00:45:55.797
but neither have I
sent any message.

665
00:45:56.214 --> 00:45:58.337
If he wrote letters.
it would be to you.

666
00:45:58.341 --> 00:46:00.427
You were always his favorite.

667
00:46:00.885 --> 00:46:02.595
Strange there has been no word.

668
00:46:03.263 --> 00:46:06.387
Otto Hightower is
ever-resourceful.

669
00:46:06.391 --> 00:46:08.935
He will send news when
there is news to send.

670
00:46:12.230 --> 00:46:13.936
I often wonder what
life could've been

671
00:46:13.940 --> 00:46:16.234
if he had brought
you to court instead.

672
00:46:18.653 --> 00:46:20.276
I'm the eldest son.

673
00:46:20.280 --> 00:46:22.361
It was right that I
was raised at Oldtown.

674
00:46:22.365 --> 00:46:23.904
But you were eight years
of age and motherless.

675
00:46:23.908 --> 00:46:25.239
It must've been difficult.

676
00:46:25.243 --> 00:46:27.912
(sighs) You get on
with it. don't you?

677
00:46:29.497 --> 00:46:31.499
When there isn't any choice.

678
00:46:34.919 --> 00:46:36.338
My son. Daeron...

679
00:46:39.632 --> 00:46:41.259
what's he like?

680
00:46:41.843 --> 00:46:45.180
- Does he not write to you?
- Less and less these days.

681
00:46:47.807 --> 00:46:49.434
Ten-and-six now.

682
00:46:50.977 --> 00:46:53.980
Letters. perhaps. hold
less of his interest.

683
00:46:58.485 --> 00:47:00.487
He's stalwart.

684
00:47:01.363 --> 00:47:02.405
Clever.

685
00:47:02.822 --> 00:47:05.825
As adept with his lute
as he is with his sword.

686
00:47:07.035 --> 00:47:08.783
And a feature in
the fancies of many

687
00:47:08.787 --> 00:47:11.039
a young lady. I'll wager.

688
00:47:15.210 --> 00:47:16.628
He's kind.

689
00:47:20.507 --> 00:47:22.133
That's good.

690
00:47:24.177 --> 00:47:28.431
- Kindness is a quality I've found lacking in his brothers.
- Mm.

691
00:47:28.807 --> 00:47:31.059
You did well to
send him to ward.

692
00:47:31.643 --> 00:47:33.599
Yes. it seems the Red Keep.

693
00:47:33.603 --> 00:47:35.184
for all its privileges.

694
00:47:35.188 --> 00:47:38.938
may. in fact. be a less
than salubrious environment

695
00:47:38.942 --> 00:47:40.819
for the forming of young men.

696
00:47:42.153 --> 00:47:44.989
Was it the court or
was it their mother?

697
00:47:47.158 --> 00:47:49.160
I'm sure you did your best.

698
00:47:55.041 --> 00:47:57.669
I must join Ser Criston.

699
00:47:58.378 --> 00:48:01.293
Wish us luck. sister.

700
00:48:01.297 --> 00:48:03.629
I shall pray to the Warrior
for your safe return.

701
00:48:03.633 --> 00:48:05.260
(Gwayne chuckles)

702
00:48:06.594 --> 00:48:07.846
Mm...

703
00:48:09.055 --> 00:48:10.265
Farewell.

704
00:48:13.601 --> 00:48:16.604
(solemn music playing)

705
00:48:32.287 --> 00:48:34.289
♪

706
00:48:46.593 --> 00:48:49.091
(crickets chirping)

707
00:48:49.095 --> 00:48:51.389
(music fades out)

708
00:48:52.307 --> 00:48:53.725
Your Grace.

709
00:48:56.728 --> 00:48:58.563
This one stopped singing.

710
00:48:59.731 --> 00:49:01.733
Isn't that strange?

711
00:49:02.484 --> 00:49:06.112
(inhales) I thought we
might light a candle.

712
00:49:07.280 --> 00:49:08.740
For Aegon...

713
00:49:10.116 --> 00:49:12.118
and all our lost souls.

714
00:49:22.337 --> 00:49:24.377
(street chatter)

715
00:49:24.381 --> 00:49:27.592
(light. tense music playing)

716
00:49:36.768 --> 00:49:38.766
(dog whimpers)

717
00:49:38.770 --> 00:49:40.772
(smallfolk shouting)

718
00:49:43.441 --> 00:49:45.147
Hugh: You. where'd
you get that food?!

719
00:49:45.151 --> 00:49:46.732
- Rhaenyra's ships.
- Ships?

720
00:49:46.736 --> 00:49:48.150
They came ashore in
the middle of the night

721
00:49:48.154 --> 00:49:49.443
with gifts from the queen.

722
00:49:49.447 --> 00:49:51.491
She thinks of us. even now!

723
00:49:51.950 --> 00:49:54.953
(dramatic music playing)

724
00:50:00.875 --> 00:50:02.502
(shouting)

725
00:50:06.131 --> 00:50:07.340
Give me that!

726
00:50:08.633 --> 00:50:11.469
- (fighting. grunting)
- Give it to me!

727
00:50:14.347 --> 00:50:16.016
(horse neighs)

728
00:50:16.307 --> 00:50:18.264
knight: Get out of the way!

729
00:50:18.268 --> 00:50:20.307
♪

730
00:50:20.311 --> 00:50:21.980
(panting)

731
00:50:24.816 --> 00:50:26.814
♪

732
00:50:26.818 --> 00:50:29.487
(smallfolk shouting in streets)

733
00:50:32.407 --> 00:50:34.409
(music quiets)

734
00:50:35.201 --> 00:50:37.450
(smallfolk shouting nearby)

735
00:50:37.454 --> 00:50:41.203
Your Graces... we
must leave. now.

736
00:50:41.207 --> 00:50:43.251
(bell tolling)

737
00:50:44.753 --> 00:50:46.876
(smallfolk shouting)

738
00:50:46.880 --> 00:50:48.923
Get the queens to
the wheelhouse!

739
00:50:52.844 --> 00:50:55.347
Mind your flanks.
Protect your corners.

740
00:50:57.265 --> 00:51:00.226
Keep moving. This
way. Your Grace.

741
00:51:02.437 --> 00:51:04.226
'Tis the Queen of Fishes!

742
00:51:04.230 --> 00:51:06.187
- (Alicent grunts)
- (Helaena gasps)

743
00:51:06.191 --> 00:51:07.897
Rickard Thorne: Keep moving!

744
00:51:07.901 --> 00:51:11.359
- (Helaena gasps)
- Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

745
00:51:11.363 --> 00:51:12.693
Alicent Hightower:
Get to the wheelhouse!

746
00:51:12.697 --> 00:51:14.028
Smallfolk: Long
live Queen Rhaenyra!

747
00:51:14.032 --> 00:51:15.863
Helaena! (grunts)

748
00:51:15.867 --> 00:51:17.365
Your Grace!

749
00:51:17.369 --> 00:51:18.699
(shouting)

750
00:51:18.703 --> 00:51:20.701
- My queen!
- Leon Estermont: Get off!

751
00:51:20.705 --> 00:51:23.537
- No! No!
- (yelling)

752
00:51:23.541 --> 00:51:25.381
- (crowd gasps)
- Alicent: Sheathe your swords!

753
00:51:26.961 --> 00:51:28.542
Sheathe your swords!

754
00:51:28.546 --> 00:51:30.878
- (crowd yelling)
- (knight shouting)

755
00:51:30.882 --> 00:51:32.421
Rickard: You heard the queen!

756
00:51:32.425 --> 00:51:34.094
Sheathe those swords!

757
00:51:42.102 --> 00:51:44.396
- No!
- (Helaena panicking)

758
00:51:45.397 --> 00:51:47.561
- Get back!
- Go. Helaena. go!

759
00:51:47.565 --> 00:51:49.730
Rickard: Out of my
way! Out of my way!

760
00:51:49.734 --> 00:51:51.736
(grunting. fighting)

761
00:51:56.324 --> 00:51:58.326
- (Leon yelling)
- knight: Estermont!

762
00:51:59.452 --> 00:52:02.789
Rickard: My Queens!
This way. inside!

763
00:52:03.331 --> 00:52:05.913
(Leon yelling)

764
00:52:05.917 --> 00:52:08.958
(tense music playing)

765
00:52:08.962 --> 00:52:11.131
(both panting)

766
00:52:13.258 --> 00:52:15.256
(music stops)

767
00:52:15.260 --> 00:52:18.430
(bell tolling) - smallfolk:
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

768
00:52:20.140 --> 00:52:22.805
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

769
00:52:22.809 --> 00:52:24.974
(shouting)

770
00:52:24.978 --> 00:52:26.646
Rickard: Run them
down if you must.

771
00:52:28.440 --> 00:52:30.813
Ride! Ride!

772
00:52:30.817 --> 00:52:33.941
(tense music resumes)

773
00:52:33.945 --> 00:52:35.947
(horse neighs)

774
00:52:43.121 --> 00:52:45.123
(music intensifies)

775
00:52:57.135 --> 00:52:59.133
(birds cawing)

776
00:52:59.137 --> 00:53:01.389
(music fades out)

777
00:53:01.973 --> 00:53:04.309
- (Aegon groaning)
- (footsteps approach)

778
00:53:07.729 --> 00:53:09.477
Larys Strong: No more.

779
00:53:09.481 --> 00:53:11.812
- My lord. Only...
- (Aegon wincing)

780
00:53:11.816 --> 00:53:13.314
...the Grand Maester
instructed me to.

781
00:53:13.318 --> 00:53:15.858
The king will be most
eager for his draught.

782
00:53:15.862 --> 00:53:17.151
in an hour.

783
00:53:17.155 --> 00:53:19.157
(Aegon grunting)

784
00:53:21.701 --> 00:53:23.703
(door opens)

785
00:53:28.208 --> 00:53:29.830
(door closes)

786
00:53:29.834 --> 00:53:32.500
The drink takes the pain away.

787
00:53:32.504 --> 00:53:35.461
- but it dulls your mind.
- (Aegon grunting)

788
00:53:35.465 --> 00:53:36.671
Oh. take heart. Your Grace.

789
00:53:36.675 --> 00:53:38.673
you've already written
yourself into legend.

790
00:53:38.677 --> 00:53:40.887
You survived dragon fire.

791
00:53:43.890 --> 00:53:45.850
But I'm afraid you
will never be whole.

792
00:53:47.352 --> 00:53:49.938
{\an8}Orwyle has exhausted
his abilities.

793
00:53:50.897 --> 00:53:52.524
{\an8}He's bound your leg...

794
00:53:54.526 --> 00:53:56.732
{\an8}but you will never run again.

795
00:53:56.736 --> 00:53:58.234
(shallow breathing)

796
00:53:58.238 --> 00:54:00.152
Your mind...

797
00:54:00.156 --> 00:54:02.196
is all that remains to you.

798
00:54:02.200 --> 00:54:04.202
I do not say that gladly.

799
00:54:08.039 --> 00:54:10.037
I came screaming into the world

800
00:54:10.041 --> 00:54:13.086
in the bowels of one of
Harren's great towers.

801
00:54:15.046 --> 00:54:18.045
My lungs were
strong. but my foot

802
00:54:18.049 --> 00:54:20.218
so twisted that...

803
00:54:21.302 --> 00:54:24.305
my father named it sorcery.

804
00:54:25.640 --> 00:54:27.263
Accusing a member
of our household

805
00:54:27.267 --> 00:54:31.312
of casting... maligned spells.

806
00:54:34.065 --> 00:54:35.483
{\an8}(softly) Well.

807
00:54:36.317 --> 00:54:38.524
{\an8}People will pity you

808
00:54:38.528 --> 00:54:40.901
{\an8}either behind your back...

809
00:54:40.905 --> 00:54:42.737
{\an8}or in your presence.

810
00:54:42.741 --> 00:54:44.200
(cries)

811
00:54:44.576 --> 00:54:46.578
And they will stare...

812
00:54:48.747 --> 00:54:50.749
at you. at you...

813
00:54:53.418 --> 00:54:54.669
or turn away.

814
00:54:58.465 --> 00:55:00.925
And they will underestimate you.

815
00:55:02.927 --> 00:55:04.967
And this will be your advantage.

816
00:55:04.971 --> 00:55:07.265
No. n... No.

817
00:55:10.101 --> 00:55:11.686
(Aegon coughs)

818
00:55:13.980 --> 00:55:15.978
Your brother rules
in your place now.

819
00:55:15.982 --> 00:55:19.027
which means that your
life is in danger.

820
00:55:21.029 --> 00:55:23.281
But I think you know that.

821
00:55:27.827 --> 00:55:29.287
(struggling) Help me.

822
00:55:31.623 --> 00:55:32.624
(shudders)

823
00:55:38.213 --> 00:55:40.298
(eerie sounds)

824
00:55:44.636 --> 00:55:46.638
(person crying)

825
00:56:15.041 --> 00:56:16.251
Brother.

826
00:56:18.878 --> 00:56:20.880
(crying) Daemon. she's gone.

827
00:56:34.019 --> 00:56:35.687
I'm sorry.

828
00:56:41.693 --> 00:56:43.528
You needed me.

829
00:56:45.864 --> 00:56:47.699
I'm here now.

830
00:56:48.408 --> 00:56:50.410
(Viserys weeping)

831
00:56:56.958 --> 00:56:58.626
I'm here now.

832
00:57:04.090 --> 00:57:05.717
Simon Strong: Your Grace.

833
00:57:08.470 --> 00:57:12.307
Sorrowful news from
Riverrun. my king.

834
00:57:13.224 --> 00:57:15.310
Lord Grover is dead.

835
00:57:17.395 --> 00:57:20.895
Uhh... the old man.

836
00:57:20.899 --> 00:57:21.900
Indeed.

837
00:57:22.734 --> 00:57:27.113
Young Oscar Tully is now Lord
Paramount of the Riverlands.

838
00:57:29.741 --> 00:57:32.073
What was the manner of
Lord Grover's passing?

839
00:57:32.077 --> 00:57:34.746
- Well. he'd been ill. of course.
- Mm-hmm.

840
00:57:35.580 --> 00:57:38.079
Riverrun's maesters...

841
00:57:38.083 --> 00:57:40.289
have been at their wits' end.

842
00:57:40.293 --> 00:57:42.583
Our own healer. Alys Rivers.

843
00:57:42.587 --> 00:57:45.753
volunteered her renowned skills.

844
00:57:45.757 --> 00:57:47.634
She plied her craft. but...

845
00:57:49.761 --> 00:57:51.763
there was naught
more to be done.

846
00:58:01.189 --> 00:58:02.816
(crying)

847
00:58:15.453 --> 00:58:17.455
(birds cawing)

848
00:58:20.333 --> 00:58:23.336
- (indistinct chatter)
- (dragon roars)

849
00:58:29.718 --> 00:58:31.340
worker: Hey. look!

850
00:58:31.344 --> 00:58:33.426
(Seasmoke screeches)

851
00:58:33.430 --> 00:58:36.470
Get inside! Hurry!

852
00:58:36.474 --> 00:58:38.476
(all yelling)

853
00:58:46.568 --> 00:58:47.902
(roars)

854
00:58:48.319 --> 00:58:49.525
(grunts)

855
00:58:49.529 --> 00:58:51.197
(panting)

856
00:58:54.701 --> 00:58:56.703
(tense music playing)

857
00:58:57.871 --> 00:58:59.873
(Seasmoke screeches)

858
00:59:06.504 --> 00:59:07.505
(roars)

859
00:59:10.008 --> 00:59:12.260
♪

860
00:59:12.886 --> 00:59:14.512
(screeches)

861
00:59:23.229 --> 00:59:25.186
{\an8}- (grunting)
- (music stops)

862
00:59:25.190 --> 00:59:26.854
(panting)

863
00:59:26.858 --> 00:59:28.860
(birds cawing)

864
00:59:36.868 --> 00:59:39.033
- (tense music resumes)
- (gasps)

865
00:59:39.037 --> 00:59:40.288
(roars)

866
00:59:42.415 --> 00:59:44.042
(grumbling)

867
00:59:52.425 --> 00:59:55.216
♪

868
00:59:55.220 --> 00:59:57.222
(heavy breathing)

869
01:00:06.231 --> 01:00:09.730
(music fades out)

870
01:00:09.734 --> 01:00:13.025
Mysaria: Your banners were carried
from the ship into the city.

871
01:00:13.029 --> 01:00:15.194
They went as far as the
gates of the Red Keep

872
01:00:15.198 --> 01:00:16.529
before they were turned away.

873
01:00:16.533 --> 01:00:18.739
It is. as we hoped. a
warning to the usurpers

874
01:00:18.743 --> 01:00:21.788
that you have strength
beyond what they accredited.

875
01:00:23.915 --> 01:00:25.750
I thought you'd be pleased.

876
01:00:27.585 --> 01:00:29.587
I do not think I
can win this war.

877
01:00:31.923 --> 01:00:33.379
I think you are tired.

878
01:00:33.383 --> 01:00:36.261
My own son questions
my capabilities.

879
01:00:38.680 --> 01:00:40.682
He thinks I need
Daemon at my side.

880
01:00:43.101 --> 01:00:47.689
- And Daemon himself.
- He has ever done what suits Daemon.

881
01:00:52.193 --> 01:00:54.446
He was everything
I wanted to be.

882
01:00:55.780 --> 01:00:56.948
Carefree.

883
01:00:57.949 --> 01:00:59.367
And dangerous.

884
01:01:00.994 --> 01:01:02.203
A man.

885
01:01:03.538 --> 01:01:05.578
And I was what he wanted.

886
01:01:05.582 --> 01:01:07.413
Cherished by my father.

887
01:01:07.417 --> 01:01:09.457
and made my father's heir.

888
01:01:09.461 --> 01:01:11.713
We were halves of a whole.

889
01:01:14.507 --> 01:01:16.509
(whispers) He's
never been at peace.

890
01:01:18.636 --> 01:01:19.967
(normal) He wished
to possess me.

891
01:01:19.971 --> 01:01:22.136
but not to be possessed

892
01:01:22.140 --> 01:01:23.846
and to see me take
hold. finally.

893
01:01:23.850 --> 01:01:26.519
of what he always
believed to be his.

894
01:01:28.980 --> 01:01:30.690
I fear what he may now do.

895
01:01:37.405 --> 01:01:39.445
I fear he may have
turned against me.

896
01:01:39.449 --> 01:01:41.822
It is more his way to disappear.

897
01:01:41.826 --> 01:01:44.245
In either case. I
have lost him...

898
01:01:45.163 --> 01:01:47.161
and Caraxes with him.

899
01:01:47.165 --> 01:01:48.996
Rhaenys and her dragon are dead.

900
01:01:49.000 --> 01:01:51.499
I have Syrax and
two young beasts.

901
01:01:51.503 --> 01:01:53.709
We cannot take on Vhagar alone.

902
01:01:53.713 --> 01:01:57.926
- And I have no army.
- You have the Velaryon fleet and the men who fight in it.

903
01:01:59.552 --> 01:02:01.012
It's not enough.

904
01:02:02.222 --> 01:02:04.845
And even if we
somehow prevailed.

905
01:02:04.849 --> 01:02:06.013
how will I rule a kingdom

906
01:02:06.017 --> 01:02:07.852
when my own son doubts me?

907
01:02:08.853 --> 01:02:09.854
You have me.

908
01:02:12.691 --> 01:02:16.111
You have my thanks... Truly.

909
01:02:28.748 --> 01:02:30.959
It was my father.

910
01:02:36.548 --> 01:02:38.341
I was still a child.

911
01:02:38.883 --> 01:02:42.887
He... had his pleasure with me.

912
01:02:43.555 --> 01:02:45.386
And when. after
many months of this.

913
01:02:45.390 --> 01:02:50.061
it became evident that
his seed had taken root.

914
01:02:57.777 --> 01:02:59.988
There is a scar here as well.

915
01:03:01.656 --> 01:03:03.908
I cannot bear children.

916
01:03:05.744 --> 01:03:07.412
He left me for dead...

917
01:03:08.913 --> 01:03:10.081
but I lived.

918
01:03:10.623 --> 01:03:14.206
- (softly) I'm so sorry.
- Swore to myself I would never trust another.

919
01:03:14.210 --> 01:03:18.419
And... that oath
has stood me well.

920
01:03:18.423 --> 01:03:20.755
This world is cold and cruel.

921
01:03:20.759 --> 01:03:24.717
and there are few in
it who are steadfast.

922
01:03:24.721 --> 01:03:28.725
You. I think. are steadfast.

923
01:03:29.434 --> 01:03:33.271
You have seen me as
worthy. as an equal. even.

924
01:03:34.272 --> 01:03:36.691
Because of that.
I will serve you.

925
01:03:37.275 --> 01:03:40.111
I believe you are
meant to be queen.

926
01:04:16.189 --> 01:04:18.817
(both breathing heavily)

927
01:04:27.742 --> 01:04:30.745
(light music playing)

928
01:04:47.846 --> 01:04:50.265
- (knocks at door)
- (door opens)

929
01:04:51.516 --> 01:04:54.477
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

930
01:04:55.186 --> 01:04:58.978
The dragon Seasmoke has been
sighted flying over Spicetown.

931
01:04:58.982 --> 01:05:00.730
Yes. he does that.

932
01:05:00.734 --> 01:05:02.402
From what we have heard...

933
01:05:02.944 --> 01:05:04.362
he has a rider.

934
01:05:04.779 --> 01:05:08.033
- Mysaria: Who?
- Impossible to tell from the ground.

935
01:05:08.742 --> 01:05:11.286
- The Greens?
- I don't know who else it could be.

936
01:05:11.703 --> 01:05:13.246
Shall I summon your counsel?

937
01:05:16.041 --> 01:05:19.044
(tense music playing)

938
01:05:21.713 --> 01:05:23.715
(Syrax roars)

939
01:05:34.726 --> 01:05:36.227
Jacaerys Velaryon: Mother!

940
01:05:41.232 --> 01:05:43.234
♪

941
01:05:48.406 --> 01:05:49.616
(roars)

942
01:05:58.583 --> 01:06:01.753
(light. curious music playing)

943
01:06:33.118 --> 01:06:35.120
♪

944
01:06:36.305 --> 01:07:36.155
